headline: W.R. Berkley: Solid Q4 But Structurally Expensive
summary: W.R. Berkley (WRB) is a hold: strong underwriting, 21% ROE and rising investment income, but valuation looks full near fair value.

headline: W. R. Berkley Corporation (WRB) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
W.R. Berkley (WRB) Q4 Earnings and Revenues Lag Estimates
summary: W.R. Berkley (WRB) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of -0.59% and -0.94%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: W. R. Berkley (NYSE:WRB) Misses Q4 CY2025 Sales Expectations
summary: Property casualty insurer W. R. Berkley (NYSE:WRB) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales only rose 1.5% year on year to $3.72 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.13 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
